    <text id="A8510T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>John B. Coles asks John H. McCue to bring him five pounds of maple sugar back
                    from Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1857-04-22">April the 22<hi rend="super">nd</hi> 1857</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I write you a few lines to ask a particular favor of you to get me about 5 <abbr
                        expan="pounds">lbs</abbr> of Maple Sugar when in Staunton the best I saw was
                    at Staples &amp; Martins the harder &amp; clearer it is the better <del
                        hand="h1">it is</del> you will find the price about 20<hi rend="super"
                    >c</hi> per <abbr expan="pound">lb</abbr> for so small a quantity you may meet
                    with a safe opportunity <orig reg="someone">some one</orig>
                    <orig reg="coming">comeing</orig> over to our Superior Court, if you will send
                    it to Mr <unclear>Wittmore</unclear> or Mr <unclear>Arnole</unclear> at <orig
                        reg="Waynesboro">Waynesborough</orig> either of them would take care of it
                    &amp; send it over either to Mr Dickinson's or
                    <unclear>Fergreson's</unclear> our Post office Mr Albertson's frequently sending
                    over to his plantation. But if you will do me the favor to write me a few lines
                    to Greenfield if I learn the sugar has been sent to <orig reg="Waynesboro"
                        >Waynesborough</orig> will send over after it. I suppose almost every day
                    you could meet with a safe opportunity to <orig reg="Waynesboro"
                    >Waynesborough</orig>. You will confer a very great favor by attending to it as
                    soon as you receive this &amp; write me without delay &amp; will send
                    you or hand you the money at sight &amp; will probably be at Staunton in a
                    week or two</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours very <abbr expan="Respectfully">Respty</abbr></salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="John">Jno.</abbr> B. Coles.</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">P. S. It It will be best to send it to <orig
                            reg="Waynesboro">Waynesborough</orig> to either of the gentlemen
                        mentioned above have it <orig reg="wrapped">wrapted</orig> up in a double
                        paper &amp; my name put on it.<lb/>J.B.C <name type="recipient"><abbr
                                expan="John">Jno.</abbr> H. McCue, <abbr expan="Esquire"
                            >Esqr.</abbr></name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
